race.comment: ALL PLAY (3) pulled up with an issue following his only run last campaign and was given a break following that effort. He looks to be back on song from what we've seen at the trials recently however and the inside barrier is a big tick for him. Can land in a positive position and return on a winning note. KAY TEE WHY (6) won well as a $1.60 pop at Belmont last start when smashed in betting. His record here is just as good, being 2/2 at this track and trip. Fitter for that run and with Pike sticking, there's no reason why he can't repeat the dose. GINNIVAN (1) finished 1.3L off KAY TEE WHY last start and does meet him better at the weights today after the claim of Cooper. His record here is a slight niggle, but he has good early speed and he's sure to give a bold sight third-up. SILVER EYE (4) disappointed last start after a big win fresh. They've tinkered with his gear again, so he can bounce back. TOO DARDY (9) looks better placed here today and can be in the finish.
